main event: A bright lighted object was sighted over the Orlando, Florida area on November 11, 1966 between 11:25 PM and 11:45 PM.
interesting points: The object was first observed in an elliptical path at high altitude, then descended rapidly and leveled off near the horizon.
The object had a bright color, possibly red, and flashing lights around the edges.
After leveling off, the object remained stationary for several minutes, then moved erratically at a rapid speed before disappearing.
The object was estimated to be much larger than a conventional aircraft.
Three different observers reported the sighting within a short period of time.
result: Probable aircraft, but could not be conclusively identified
sighted object: A bright lighted object, possibly red in color, with flashing lights around the edges
